('crowdin',
 'Crowdin',
 'Community-powered localization platform for software and open-source projects',
 'Crowdin is a cloud-based localization management platform that serves both commercial software teams and open-source communities, making it the most versatile translation tool for projects that need to involve community contributors alongside professional translators. The platform supports over 50 file formats and integrates with GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and major CMS platforms to automatically pull new strings into translation workflows as content is published. Crowdin AI translates content using pre-integrated providers including DeepL, Microsoft Translator, and Google Translate, while the Translation Memory engine learns from every approved translation to improve suggestions over time. For open-source projects, the crowdsourcing feature enables community members to contribute translations and vote on suggestions, reducing costs while building community engagement. The in-context localisation editor shows translators the live website so strings are translated in context without screenshots or separate reference materials. Enterprise features include custom workflows, QA checks for consistency and terminology, and dedicated support.',
