('poeditor',
 'POEditor',
 'Lightweight localization management for developers and small teams',
 'POEditor is a straightforward online localization platform for software developers and small teams that need to manage translation projects without the overhead of an enterprise TMS. The platform supports all major software localization file formats including PO, POT, XLIFF, JSON, Android XML, iOS Strings, ARB, and CSV, making it compatible with every major development framework. Developers connect GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket repositories to automatically sync new strings into POEditor when code is committed, and pull approved translations back into the codebase without manual file handling. Contributors can be added as translators, with configurable roles from viewer to administrator, enabling teams to involve professional translators, community volunteers, or internal bilingual team members. Machine translation from DeepL, Google Translate, and Microsoft Translator is available for pre-translation of new strings. Translation Memory stores approved translations and suggests them when identical or similar strings appear in future projects. The pricing model charges per project contributor rather than per word, making costs predictable for ongoing localisation projects. POEditor is the most cost-effective professional localization platform for development teams managing 2 to 20 languages.',
